                       pom.xml
The pom.xml file is the Project Object Model (POM) file for a Maven project. It's an XML file that contains project configuration information
1. Project metadata: Group ID, artifact ID, version, and packaging type.
2. Dependencies: List of dependencies required by the project.
3. Build configuration: Compiler settings, plugins, and other build-related configuration.
4. Repositories: List of repositories to search for dependencies.
           uses of pom.xml:
1. Dependency management: Declares dependencies and their versions.
2. Build automation: Configures the build process, including compilation, testing, and packaging.
3. Project configuration: Stores project metadata and configuration.
4. Plugin management: Configures plugins used in the build process.

Example pom.xml structure:

<project xmlns="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
  xsi:schemaLocation="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 http://maven.apache.org/maven-v4_0_0.xsd">
  <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>

  <groupId>com.example</groupId>
  <artifactId>myproject</artifactId>
  <version>1.0</version>
  <packaging>jar</packaging>

  <name>My Project</name>

  <dependencies>
    <!-- dependencies -->
  </dependencies>

  <build>
    <!-- build configuration -->
  </build>
</project>
